## What I polished — `src/blog/people/drafts/Rose-Blackpink.md`

This draft came in unusually strong. It had already been through a fresh-eyes review and a substantive second pass, and both did the heavy lifting (BLACKPINK grounding, the APT.-contradiction beat, motif trims, the 3-vs-4 de-dupe). So this was a genuine polish pass, not a rescue. I made two surgical edits and left the rest alone:

1. **Killed a fourth-wall / essay-about-essay tell.** The "Reading the Comments" section had *"That is the one place the theory earns a full paragraph, because Rosé lives it more nakedly than almost any star will admit to."* That's the writer narrating their own structure, a subtle AI/writerly tic. Rewrote to point at Rosé, not the paragraph: *"Rosé lives that wiring more nakedly than almost any star will admit to."*

2. **Fixed a clunky trailing preposition.** *"the most social-Four environment a person could be built inside of"* → *"...a person could be dropped into."*

